# Flags

Flags are boolean state values.

Current examples:

```md
room:kitchen.visited
room:kitchen.viewed
feature:kitchen.table.examined
```

We should keep these, but expand the flag system so authors can create custom flags.

## Flag Examples

```md
room:kitchen.visited
room:kitchen.viewed
feature:kitchen.table.examined
item:apple.taken
item:apple.onTable
npc:ratKing.met
npc:guard.distracted
door:cellar.unlocked
quest:findLantern.started
quest:findLantern.completed
world:ratsReleased
world:stormStarted
```

## Author-Created Flags

Authors should be able to define custom flags from the UI.

Examples:

```md
kitchen.applePlacedOnTable
pantry.ratsAttracted
guard.hasSeenPlayer
mirror.hasBeenBroken
lantern.isLit
bell.hasBeenRung
```

## Flag Condition Types

Authors should be able to check:

```md
Flag is true
Flag is false
Flag exists
Flag does not exist
```

## Flag Effect Types

Authors should be able to:

```md
Set flag true
Set flag false
Toggle flag
Clear flag
```

