# Item Locations

The current inventory is a list of item IDs. That supports simple take/drop logic, but richer interactions need item locations.

Recommended:

```md
itemLocations: Record<ItemId, ItemLocation>
```

Possible locations:

```md
inventory
room
container
surface
npc
hidden
destroyed
```

## Item Location Examples

```md
apple is in player inventory
apple is in room kitchen
apple is on table
apple is inside cabinet
apple is held by npc cook
apple is hidden under bed
apple is destroyed
```

## Why This Matters

The apple-on-table example requires knowing that the apple is specifically on the table, not merely removed from inventory.

This lets later logic check:

```md
If apple is on table
If rats are not already present
If 3 turns have passed
Then move rats to kitchen
```

## Item Location Conditions

Authors should be able to check:

```md
Player has item
Player does not have item
Item is in current room
Item is in specific room
Item is on surface
Item is in container
Item is held by NPC
Item is hidden
Item is destroyed
Item is visible to player
Item is reachable by player
```

## Item Location Effects

Authors should be able to:

```md
Add item to inventory
Remove item from inventory
Move item to room
Move item to current room
Place item on surface
Place item in container
Give item to NPC
Hide item
Reveal item
Destroy item
Duplicate item
```

