# Scheduled Events

The apple attracting rats requires delayed behavior.

The command itself should not need to immediately spawn rats. It should be able to schedule an event.

## Scheduled Event Examples

```md
ratsArrive in 3 turns
stormStarts in 5 turns
guardReturns in 2 turns
appleRots in 10 turns
candleBurnsOut in 4 turns
```

## Scheduled Event Data

A scheduled event should include:

```md
id
eventId
triggerType
triggerAtTurn
remainingTurns
conditions
effects
message
repeat
cancelIf
```

## Time Types

The engine may start with turn-based timing.

Recommended timing options:

```md
After N turns
At turn number N
When player enters room
When player leaves room
When flag becomes true
When item reaches location
Every N turns
Once per room visit
Immediately after command
```

Real-time timers are probably unnecessary for the first version.

## Scheduled Event Conditions

Scheduled events should still check conditions before firing.

Example:

```md
Event:
ratsArrive

After:
3 turns

Only if:
- apple is on kitchen table
- rats are not already in kitchen
- player has not cleaned table

Then:
- Move rats to kitchen
- Set flag kitchen.ratsPresent true
- Show message if player is in kitchen:
  "You hear skittering under the floorboards. Rats pour into the kitchen, drawn by the apple."
```

If the player removes the apple before the event fires:

```md
Cancel if:
- apple is not on kitchen table
```

## Scheduled Event Effects

Events should use the same effect system as commands.

That means scheduled events can:

```md
Set flags
Move items
Move NPCs
Change object states
Show messages
Unlock exits
Change room descriptions
Start quests
End quests
Schedule more events
Cancel events
```

