# Safety and Validation

The editor should prevent invalid authored commands.

## Validation Rules

```md
Every command must have a name
Every command must have at least one trigger
Every referenced room/item/NPC/feature must exist
Every scheduled event ID must exist
Every condition must be complete
Every effect must be complete
No duplicate IDs
No circular event loops without repeat limits
No unreachable command warnings
No ambiguous target warnings where possible
```

## Warnings

Examples:

```md
This command references an item that does not exist.
This event schedules itself every turn forever.
This command can never run because its conditions conflict.
This command has lower priority than a broader command and may never be reached.
This message uses {object.name}, but the command has no object target.
```

